{"uuid": "fbb20887-a8ea-4db9-8fe3-84794bca34a7", "id": 20489, "date": "2020-08-26T05:00:00", "date_gmt": "2020-08-26T12:00:00", "guid": {"rendered": "http://estreetshuffle.com/?p=20489"}, "modified": "2023-01-01T17:12:31", "modified_gmt": "2023-01-02T01:12:31", "slug": "cover-me-billy-bragg-mansion-on-the-hill", "status": "publish", "type": "post", "link": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/2020/08/26/cover-me-billy-bragg-mansion-on-the-hill/", "title": {"rendered": "Cover Me, Billy Bragg: Mansion on the Hill"}, "content": {"rendered": "<p>It&#8217;s been a while since we&#8217;ve featured a cover from the wonderful 2003 Springsteen tribute compilation,\u00a0<em>Light of Day.\u00a0</em></p>\n<p><i>Light of Day </i>features a host of names and voices that will be familiar to anyone who&#8217;s attended the Asbury Park music festival that goes by the same name, each covering a tune from the Springsteen songbook&#8211;some well-known, others obscure.</p>\n<p>One of my favorite tracks is Billy Bragg&#8217;s Fats Domino-inspired arrangement of &#8220;<a href=\"https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/2022/03/06/roll-of-the-dice-mansion-on-the-hill/\">Mansion on the Hill.</a>&#8221;</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"Billy Bragg &amp; The Blokes - Mansion On The Hill\" width=\"758\" height=\"426\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/cBY7QPDYEM8?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen></iframe></div>\n<p>&#8220;Mansion on the Hill&#8221; is a song steeped in nostalgia, and it&#8217;s a tough song to play uptempo without losing that. Bragg figured out a way to do it, though, rooting his band arrangement in the sound of popular music from the time Bruce writes about in the song.</p>\n<p>It&#8217;s a brilliant concept, and Bragg and The Blokes execute it perfectly.</p>